articles.title: Arm IPO delivers $84mn fees bonanza for its advisers - Financial Times
articles.description: Non-underwriting costs of flotation are the highest Wall Street has seen for five years, according to FT analysis
articles.content:
Arms $5bn initial public offering this week was the most expensive in fees for five years, earning a $84mn windfall for the professional services firms that advised it, including Deloitte.
